102// CodeGenLLVM has members of type std::unique_ptr<T>. These members will be
103// instantiated in the constructor, which will requre that the type T is
104// complete at that point. Put the constructor (and destructor) here, since
105// all types should be complete here.
106CodeGenLLVM::CodeGenLLVM() = default;
107CodeGenLLVM::~CodeGenLLVM() = default;
108CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo::~DebugInfo() = default;
109
110std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM> CodeGenLLVM::Create(LLVMTarget* llvm_target) {
111 std::string target = llvm_target->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->getTarget().getName();
112 std::string factory_template = "tvm.codegen.llvm.target_";
113 void* handle = nullptr;
114 if (const PackedFunc* f = runtime::Registry::Get(factory_template + target)) {
115 handle = (*f)();
116 } else if (const PackedFunc* f = runtime::Registry::Get(factory_template + "cpu")) {
117 handle = (*f)();
118 } else {
119 LOG(FATAL) << "no factory function for codegen for target " << target;
120 }
121 if (handle) {
122 return std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM>(static_cast<CodeGenLLVM*>(handle));
123 } else {
124 LOG(FATAL) << "unable to create codegen for target " << target;
125 return nullptr; // unreachable
126 }
127}

129void CodeGenLLVM::Init(const std::string& module_name, LLVMTarget* llvm_target, bool system_lib,
130 bool dynamic_lookup, bool target_c_runtime) {
131 llvm_target_ = llvm_target;
132 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
133 builder_.reset(new IRBuilder(*ctx));
134 module_.reset(new llvm::Module(module_name, *ctx));
135 md_builder_.reset(new llvm::MDBuilder(*ctx));
136 // types
137 t_void_ = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(*ctx);
138 t_void_p_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx)->getPointerTo(GetGlobalAddressSpace());
139 t_int_ = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(*ctx);
140 t_char_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx);
141 t_int8_ = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx);
142 t_int16_ = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(*ctx);
143 t_int32_ = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(*ctx);
144 t_int64_ = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(*ctx);
145 t_float64_ = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(*ctx);
146 // meta data
147 md_very_likely_branch_ = md_builder_->createBranchWeights(1 << 20, 1);
148 md_tbaa_root_ = md_builder_->createTBAARoot("tvm-tbaa");
149 md_tbaa_alias_set_ = md_builder_->createTBAANode("tvm-alias", md_tbaa_root_);
150 InitTarget();
151}

153void CodeGenLLVM::SetFastMathFlags(llvm::FastMathFlags fmf) { builder_->setFastMathFlags(fmf); }

155void CodeGenLLVM::InitTarget() {
156 llvm::TargetMachine* tm = llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine();
157 module_->setTargetTriple(tm->getTargetTriple().str());
158 module_->setDataLayout(tm->createDataLayout());
159 data_layout_.reset(new llvm::DataLayout(module_.get()));
160 if (native_vector_bits_ == 0) {
161 const auto& arch = tm->getTargetTriple().getArch();
162 if (arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
163 // for avx512
164 native_vector_bits_ = 512;
165 } else if (arch == llvm::Triple::x86) {
166 native_vector_bits_ = 256;
167 } else if (arch == llvm::Triple::arm || arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64) {
168 native_vector_bits_ = 128;
169 } else {
170 native_vector_bits_ = 128;
171 std::string arch_name = std::string(tm->getTargetTriple().getArchName());
172 LOG(WARNING) << "Set native vector bits to be 128 for " << arch_name;
173 }
174 }
175
176#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 60
177 bool use_float16_abi = false;
178#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 150
179 // For conversions between _Float16 and float, LLVM uses runtime functions
180 // __extendhfsf2 and __truncsfhf2. On X86 up until version 14, LLVM used
181 // "uint16_t" for representing _Float16. Starting with LLVM 15, half-precision
182 // values can be passed in XMM registers (i.e. as floating-point). This happens
183 // when the compilation target has SSE2 enabled (either directly, or by enabling
184 // a feature that implies SSE2).
185 // Because the names of the conversion functions remain unchanged, it is impossible
186 // for TVM to provide them in the runtime, and have them work in both cases.
187 // To alleviate this issue, emit these functions directly into the target module
188 // after detecting whether or not to use floating-point ABI. To allow the linker
189 // to remove potential duplicates (or if they are unused), they are weak and
190 // reside in a separate section (ELF).
191 llvm::Triple::ArchType arch_type = tm->getTargetTriple().getArch();
192 if (arch_type == llvm::Triple::x86 || arch_type == llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
193 // Detect if SSE2 is enabled. This determines whether float16 ABI is used.
194 std::stringstream os;
195 const char fname[] = "test_sse2";
196 os << "target triple = \"" << llvm_target_->GetTargetTriple() << "\"\n"
197 << "define void @" << fname << "() #0 { ret void } attributes #0 = { \"target-cpu\"=\""
198 << llvm_target_->GetCPU() << "\" ";
199 if (auto&& fs = llvm_target_->GetTargetFeatureString(); !fs.empty()) {
200 os << "\"target-features\"=\"" << fs << "\" ";
201 }
202 os << "}\n";
203 auto mod = llvm_target_->GetInstance().ParseIR(os.str());
204 auto* test_sse2 = mod->getFunction(fname);
205 ICHECK(test_sse2 != nullptr) << "Module creation error";
206 use_float16_abi = tm->getSubtargetImpl(*test_sse2)->checkFeatures("+sse2");
207 }
208#endif // TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 150
209
210 // Call this function only with LLVM >= 6.0. The code it emits uses "dso_local"
211 // which was introduced in LLVM 6.
212 EmitFloat16ConversionBuiltins(use_float16_abi);
213#endif // TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 60
214}

218void CodeGenLLVM::InitFuncState() {
219 var_map_.clear();
220 alias_var_set_.clear();
221 alloc_storage_info_.clear();
222 volatile_buf_.clear();
223 analyzer_.reset(new arith::Analyzer());

225
226void CodeGenLLVM::AddFunctionInternal(const PrimFunc& f, bool ret_void) {
227 this->InitFuncState();
228
229 ICHECK_EQ(f->buffer_map.size(), 0U)
230 << "Cannot codegen function with buffer_map, please lower them first";
231
232 std::vector<llvm::Type*> param_types;
233 is_restricted_ = f->HasNonzeroAttr(tir::attr::kNoAlias);
234 for (Var param : f->params) {
235 param_types.push_back(GetLLVMType(param));
236 if (!is_restricted_ && param.dtype().is_handle()) {
237 alias_var_set_.insert(param.get());
238 }
239 }
240 // TODO(tvm-team):
241 // Update the function type to respect the ret_type field of f.
242 // Once we allow more flexibility in the PrimFunc.
243 llvm::FunctionType* ftype =
244 llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_void ? t_void_ : t_int_, param_types, false);
245
246 auto global_symbol = f->GetAttr<String>(tvm::attr::kGlobalSymbol);
247 ICHECK(global_symbol.defined())
248 << "CodeGenLLVM: Expect PrimFunc to have the global_symbol attribute";
249 function_ = module_->getFunction(MakeStringRef(global_symbol.value()));
250 if (function_ == nullptr) {
251 function_ = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
252 MakeStringRef(global_symbol.value()), module_.get());
253 }
254 function_->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::C);
255 function_->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes::DLLExportStorageClass);
256 SetTargetAttributes(function_);
257
258 // set var map and align information
259 auto arg_it = function_->arg_begin();
260 for (size_t i = 0; i < f->params.size(); ++i, ++arg_it) {
261 llvm::Argument* v = &(*arg_it);
262 const Var& var = f->params[i];
263 var_map_[var.get()] = v;
264 v->setName(std::string(var->name_hint));
265 if (is_restricted_) {
266 if (var.dtype().is_handle() && !alias_var_set_.count(var.get())) {
267 // set non alias.
268#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
269 function_->addParamAttr(i, llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
270#else
271 function_->setDoesNotAlias(i + 1);
272#endif
273 }
274 }
275 }
276 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
277 llvm::BasicBlock* entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "entry", function_);
278 builder_->SetInsertPoint(entry);
279 this->VisitStmt(f->body);
280
281 // Add alignment attribute if needed.
282#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
283 for (size_t i = 0; i < f->params.size(); ++i) {
284 const Var& var = f->params[i];
285 auto f = alloc_storage_info_.find(var.get());
286 if (f != alloc_storage_info_.end()) {
287 unsigned align = f->second.alignment;
288 if (align > 1) {
289 auto attr = llvm::Attribute::get(*ctx, llvm::Attribute::Alignment, align);
290 function_->addParamAttr(i, attr);
291 }
292 }
293 }
294#endif
295
296 if (ret_void) {
297 builder_->CreateRetVoid();
298 } else {
299 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
300 }
301}
302
303std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGenLLVM::Finish() {
304 this->AddStartupFunction();
305 for (size_t i = 0; i < link_modules_.size(); ++i) {
306 ICHECK(!llvm::Linker::linkModules(*module_, std::move(link_modules_[i])))
307 << "Failed to link modules";
308 }
309 link_modules_.clear();
310 // optimize
311 this->Optimize();
312 return std::move(module_);
313}
314
315void CodeGenLLVM::HandleImport(const std::string& code) {
316 llvm::StringRef code_str(code);
317 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> mlib;
318 if (code_str.endswith(".ll") || code_str.endswith(".bc")) {
319 mlib = llvm_target_->GetInstance().LoadIR(code);
320 } else {
321 mlib = llvm_target_->GetInstance().ParseIR(code);
322 }
323
324 mlib->setTargetTriple(llvm_target_->GetTargetTriple());
325 mlib->setDataLayout(llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->createDataLayout());
326 // mark all the functions as force inline
327 for (llvm::Function& f : mlib->functions()) {
328 f.removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
329 f.addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
330 f.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
331 }
332 // add to linker libraries.
333 this->AddLinkModule(std::move(mlib));
334}
335
336void CodeGenLLVM::AddLinkModule(std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>&& mod) {
337 link_modules_.emplace_back(std::move(mod));
338}

369void CodeGenLLVM::Optimize() {
370 // pass manager
371 FPassManager fpass(module_.get());
372 MPassManager mpass;
373 llvm::TargetMachine* tm = llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine();
374 mpass.add(llvm::createTargetTransformInfoWrapperPass(tm->getTargetIRAnalysis()));
375 fpass.add(llvm::createTargetTransformInfoWrapperPass(tm->getTargetIRAnalysis()));
376
377 // place optimization pass
378 llvm::PassManagerBuilder builder;
379
380 // Use the same opt-level as specified in TargetMachine for running passes
381 llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level opt_level = llvm_target_->GetOptLevel();
382
383 switch (opt_level) {
384 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::None:
385 builder.OptLevel = 0;
386 break;
387 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::Less:
388 builder.OptLevel = 1;
389 break;
390
391 case llvm::CodeGenOpt::Level::Default:
392 builder.OptLevel = 2;
393 break;
394
395 default:
396 // CodeGenOpt::Level::Aggressive
397 builder.OptLevel = 3;
398 }
399
400#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
401 builder.Inliner = llvm::createFunctionInliningPass(builder.OptLevel, 0, false);
402#else
403 builder.Inliner = llvm::createFunctionInliningPass(builder.OptLevel, 0);
404#endif
405 builder.LoopVectorize = true;
406 builder.SLPVectorize = true;
407 this->InitPassManagerBuilder(&builder);
408
409#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
410 tm->adjustPassManager(builder);
411#endif
412
413 builder.populateFunctionPassManager(fpass);
414 builder.populateModulePassManager(mpass);
415
416 fpass.doInitialization();
417 for (auto it = module_->begin(); it != module_->end(); ++it) {
418 fpass.run(*it);
419 }
420 fpass.doFinalization();
421 mpass.run(*module_);
422}

430llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::DTypeToLLVMType(const DataType& dtype) const {
431 if (dtype.is_handle()) {
432 ICHECK_EQ(dtype.lanes(), 1);
433 return t_void_p_;
434 }
435 if (dtype.is_void()) {
436 return t_void_;
437 }
438 llvm::Type* etype = nullptr;
439 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
440 if (dtype.is_int() || dtype.is_uint()) {
441 etype = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(*ctx, dtype.bits());
442 } else if (dtype.is_float()) {
443 switch (dtype.bits()) {
444 case 16:
445 etype = llvm::Type::getHalfTy(*ctx);
446 break;
447 case 32:
448 etype = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(*ctx);
449 break;
450 case 64:
451 etype = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(*ctx);
452 break;
453 default:
454 LOG(FATAL) << "do not support " << dtype;
455 }
456 }
457 if (dtype.lanes() != 1) {
458#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
459 return llvm::FixedVectorType::get(etype, dtype.lanes());
460#else
461 return llvm::VectorType::get(etype, dtype.lanes());
462#endif
463 } else {
464 return etype;
465 }
466} // namespace codegen
467
468llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::GetLLVMType(const Type& type) const {
469 if (auto* ptr = type.as<PrimTypeNode>()) {
470 return DTypeToLLVMType(ptr->dtype);
471 } else if (auto* ptr = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
472 // LLVM IR doesn't allow void*, so we need to recognize this
473 // pattern explicitly.
474 if (auto* primtype = ptr->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>()) {
475 if (primtype->dtype.is_void()) {
476 return t_void_p_;
477 }
478 }
479 // TODO(tvm-team) consider put storage scope into the pointer type.
480 return GetLLVMType(ptr->element_type)->getPointerTo(GetGlobalAddressSpace());
481 } else if (IsVoidType(type)) {
482 return t_void_;
483 } else {
484 LOG(FATAL) << "Type " << type << " does not have a corresponding LLVM Type";
485 return t_void_;
486 }
487}
488
489llvm::Type* CodeGenLLVM::GetLLVMType(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
490 return GetLLVMType(GetType(expr));
491}

493// Add tbaa alias information for load
494//
495// use a binary tree typed system to declare information
496// and allow alias to be distinguished across nodes.
497//
498// This trick comes from Halide's CodeGen_LLVM
499//
500void CodeGenLLVM::AddAliasInfo(llvm::Instruction* inst, const VarNode* buffer_var, PrimExpr index,
501 DataType access_dtype) {
502 if (alias_var_set_.count(buffer_var) != 0) {
503 // Mark all possibly aliased pointer as same type.
504 llvm::MDNode* meta = md_tbaa_alias_set_;
505 inst->setMetadata("tbaa", md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(meta, meta, 0));
506 return;
507 }
508
509 int64_t base = 0, width = 0;
510 arith::PVar<IntImm> pbase, pstride;
511 arith::PVar<int> planes;
512 // create meta-data for alias analysis
513 // Use a group of binary tree ranges of memory banks.
514 int64_t xwith = 0;
515 if (arith::ramp(pbase, pstride, planes).Match(index)) {
516 base = pbase.Eval()->value;
517 xwith = planes.Eval() * pstride.Eval()->value;
518 } else if (auto* ptr = index.as<tir::IntImmNode>()) {
519 base = ptr->value;
520 xwith = 1;
521 }
522 // adjust address index unit to byte
523 const int64_t unit_bit_width = 8;
524 const int64_t access_elem_bits = access_dtype.bits() * access_dtype.lanes();
525 base = base * access_elem_bits / unit_bit_width;
526 xwith = (xwith * access_elem_bits + unit_bit_width - 1) / unit_bit_width;
527 if (xwith > 0) {
528 width = 1;
529 while (width < xwith) {
530 width *= 2;
531 }
532 while (base % width) {
533 base -= base % width;
534 width *= 2;
535 }
536 }
537
538 llvm::MDNode* meta = md_tbaa_root_;
539 std::ostringstream buffer_addr;
540 buffer_addr << buffer_var;
541 meta = md_builder_->createTBAAScalarTypeNode(buffer_addr.str(), meta);
542
543 // create a tree-shape access structure.
544 if (width != 0) {
545 for (int64_t w = 1024; w >= width; w /= 2) {
546 int64_t b = (base / w) * w;
547 std::stringstream os;
548 os << buffer_var << ".w" << w << ".b" << b;
549 meta = md_builder_->createTBAAScalarTypeNode(os.str(), meta);
550 }
551 }
552 inst->setMetadata("tbaa", md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(meta, meta, 0));
553}
554
555void CodeGenLLVM::GetAlignment(DataType t, const VarNode* buf_var, const PrimExpr& index,
556 int* p_alignment, int* p_native_bits) {
557 int max_align_bits = t.bits();
558 auto it = alloc_storage_info_.find(buf_var);
559 if (it != alloc_storage_info_.end()) {
560 const StorageInfo& info = it->second;
561 *p_native_bits =
562 NativeVectorBits(runtime::StorageScope::Create(GetPtrStorageScope(GetRef<Var>(buf_var))));
563 max_align_bits = info.alignment * 8;
564 } else {
565 *p_native_bits = native_vector_bits_;
566 }
567
568 arith::ModularSet me = analyzer_->modular_set(index);
569 int64_t base = me->base;
570 int64_t coeff = me->coeff;
571
572 int align_bits = t.bits();
573 while (align_bits < max_align_bits && base % 2 == 0 && coeff % 2 == 0) {
574 base = base / 2;
575 coeff = coeff / 2;
576 align_bits *= 2;
577 }
578 if (align_bits < 8) {
579 align_bits = 8;
580 }
581 *p_alignment = align_bits / 8;
582}
583
584llvm::GlobalVariable* CodeGenLLVM::AllocateSharedMemory(DataType dtype, size_t size,
585 unsigned int shared_address_space,
586 int alignment,
587 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage) {
588 llvm::Type* type = llvm::ArrayType::get(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype), size);
589 llvm::GlobalVariable* global =
590 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, type, false, linkage, nullptr, "shmem", nullptr,
591 llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal, shared_address_space);
592#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
593 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(alignment));
594#else
595 global->setAlignment(alignment);
596#endif
597 return global;
598}

600std::unique_ptr<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo> CodeGenLLVM::CreateDebugInfo(llvm::Module* module) {
601#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
602 auto debug_info = std::make_unique<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo>();
603 debug_info->di_builder_ = std::make_unique<llvm::DIBuilder>(*module);
604#else
605 auto debug_info = llvm::make_unique<CodeGenLLVM::DebugInfo>();
606 debug_info->di_builder_ = llvm::make_unique<llvm::DIBuilder>(*module);
607#endif
608 // TODO(tulloch): pass this information through relay::Span classes to the IRModule instance?
609 debug_info->file_ = debug_info->di_builder_->createFile("model.tvm", "/tmp/");
610 debug_info->compilation_unit_ = debug_info->di_builder_->createCompileUnit(
611 llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C, debug_info->file_, "TVM", 0, "", 0, "",
612 llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugEmissionKind::FullDebug,
613 /* SplitDebugInlining */ true,
614 /* DebugInfoForProfiling */ true);
615 return debug_info;
616}

618llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateBroadcast(llvm::Value* value, int lanes) {
619#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
620 llvm::Type* type = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(value->getType(), lanes);
621#else
622 llvm::Type* type = llvm::VectorType::get(value->getType(), lanes);
623#endif
624 llvm::Constant* undef = llvm::UndefValue::get(type);
625 llvm::Constant* zero = ConstInt32(0);
626 value = builder_->CreateInsertElement(undef, value, zero);
627#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 120
628 llvm::Constant* mask = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(llvm::ElementCount::getFixed(lanes), zero);
629#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
630 llvm::Constant* mask =
631 llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(llvm::ElementCount(lanes, /*Scalable=*/false), zero);
632#else
633 llvm::Constant* mask = llvm::ConstantVector::getSplat(lanes, zero);
634#endif
635 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(value, undef, mask);
636}
637
638llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecSlice(llvm::Value* vec, int begin, int extent) {
639 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
640 if (extent == num_elems && begin == 0) return vec;
641 ICHECK(begin >= 0 && extent <= num_elems) << "Slicing out of bound!\n";
642 std::vector<llvm::Constant*> indices;
643 indices.reserve(extent);
644 for (int i = 0; i < extent; ++i) {
645 if (begin + i >= 0 && begin + i < num_elems) {
646 indices.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int32_, begin + i));
647 } else {
648 indices.push_back(llvm::UndefValue::get(t_int32_));
649 }
650 }
651 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, llvm::ConstantVector::get(indices));
652}
653
654llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecFlip(llvm::Value* vec) {
655 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
656#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
657 std::vector<int> indices;
658#else
659 std::vector<unsigned> indices;
660#endif
661 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
662 indices.push_back(num_elems - i - 1);
663 }
664 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, indices);
665}
666
667llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecPad(llvm::Value* vec, int target_lanes) {
668 llvm::Value* mask = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(DataType::Int(32, target_lanes)));
669 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(vec);
670 if (num_elems == target_lanes) return vec;
671 ICHECK_LT(num_elems, target_lanes);
672 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
673 mask = builder_->CreateInsertElement(mask, ConstInt32(i), ConstInt32(i));
674 }
675 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(vec, vec, mask);
676}
677
678llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateVecConcat(std::vector<llvm::Value*> vecs) {
679 // To allow creating vectors from scalars, convert any scalars in "vecs" to single-lane
680 // LLVM vector types.
681 for (size_t i = 0, e = vecs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
682 llvm::Value* v = vecs[i];
683 if (!v->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
684#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
685 llvm::Type* vec_ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(v->getType(), 1);
686#else
687 llvm::Type* vec_ty = llvm::VectorType::get(v->getType(), 1);
688#endif
689 vecs[i] = builder_->CreateInsertElement(llvm::UndefValue::get(vec_ty), v, ConstInt32(0));
690 }
691 }
692
693 // concat vector, tree shape reduction
694 int total_lanes = 0;
695
696 for (llvm::Value* v : vecs) {
697 total_lanes += GetVectorNumElements(v);
698 }
699 while (vecs.size() > 1) {
700 std::vector<llvm::Value*> new_vecs;
701 for (size_t i = 0; i < vecs.size() - 1; i += 2) {
702 llvm::Value* lhs = vecs[i];
703 llvm::Value* rhs = vecs[i + 1];
704 const size_t lhs_lanes = GetVectorNumElements(lhs);
705 const size_t rhs_lanes = GetVectorNumElements(rhs);
706 if (lhs_lanes < rhs_lanes) {
707 lhs = CreateVecPad(lhs, rhs_lanes);
708 } else if (rhs_lanes < lhs_lanes) {
709 rhs = CreateVecPad(rhs, lhs_lanes);
710 }
711 const size_t shared_lanes = std::max(lhs_lanes, rhs_lanes);
712#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
713 std::vector<int> mask;
714#else
715 std::vector<unsigned> mask;
716#endif
717 for (size_t i = 0; i < lhs_lanes; ++i) {
718 mask.push_back(i);
719 }
720 for (size_t i = 0; i < rhs_lanes; ++i) {
721 mask.push_back(shared_lanes + i);
722 }
723 new_vecs.push_back(builder_->CreateShuffleVector(lhs, rhs, mask));
724 }
725 if (vecs.size() % 2 != 0) {
726 new_vecs.push_back(vecs.back());
727 }
728 vecs.swap(new_vecs);
729 }
730 return CreateVecSlice(vecs[0], 0, total_lanes);
731}
732
733void CodeGenLLVM::CreateSerialFor(llvm::Value* begin, llvm::Value* end, llvm::Value* stride,
734 const Var& loop_var, const Stmt& body) {
735 llvm::BasicBlock* pre_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
736 std::string loop_var_name = loop_var->name_hint;
737 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
738 auto* for_begin = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_begin_" + loop_var_name, function_);
739 auto* for_body = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_body_" + loop_var_name, function_);
740 auto* for_end = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "for_end_" + loop_var_name, function_);
741 builder_->CreateBr(for_begin);
742 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_begin);
743 llvm::PHINode* loop_value = builder_->CreatePHI(begin->getType(), 2);
744 loop_value->setName(loop_var->name_hint.c_str());
745 loop_value->addIncoming(begin, pre_block);
746 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(loop_var.get()));
747 var_map_[loop_var.get()] = loop_value;
748 builder_->CreateCondBr(CreateLT(loop_var.dtype(), loop_value, end), for_body, for_end,
749 md_very_likely_branch_);
750 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_body);
751 this->VisitStmt(body);
752 var_map_.erase(loop_var.get());
753 llvm::Value* loop_next = CreateAdd(loop_var.dtype(), loop_value, stride);
754 loop_value->addIncoming(loop_next, builder_->GetInsertBlock());
755 builder_->CreateBr(for_begin);
756 builder_->SetInsertPoint(for_end);
757}
758
759// cast operatpr
760llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateCast(DataType from, DataType to, llvm::Value* value) {
761 llvm::Type* target = DTypeToLLVMType(to);
762 if (value->getType() == target) return value;
763 if (to.is_handle()) {
764 return builder_->CreateBitCast(value, target);
765 } else if (to.is_uint() && to.bits() == 1) {
766 if (from.is_float()) {
767 llvm::Constant* zero = llvm::ConstantFP::get(DTypeToLLVMType(from), 0.);
768 return builder_->CreateFCmpONE(value, zero);
769 } else {
770 llvm::Constant* zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(DTypeToLLVMType(from), 0);
771 return builder_->CreateICmpNE(value, zero);
772 }
773 } else if (!from.is_float() && !to.is_float()) {
774 return builder_->CreateIntCast(value, target, from.is_int());
775 } else if (from.is_float() && to.is_int()) {
776 return builder_->CreateFPToSI(value, target);
777 } else if (from.is_float() && to.is_uint()) {
778 if (to.bits() < 8) {
779 value = builder_->CreateFPToUI(value, DTypeToLLVMType(to.with_bits(8)));
780 return builder_->CreateIntCast(value, target, false);
781 } else {
782 return builder_->CreateFPToUI(value, target);
783 }
784 } else if (from.is_int() && to.is_float()) {
785 return builder_->CreateSIToFP(value, target);
786 } else if (from.is_uint() && to.is_float()) {
787 return builder_->CreateUIToFP(value, target);
788 } else {
789 ICHECK(from.is_float() && to.is_float());
790 return builder_->CreateFPCast(value, target);
791 }
792}

794llvm::Constant* CodeGenLLVM::GetGlobalConstant(llvm::Constant* const_data, const std::string& name,
795 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage_type) {
796 llvm::Type* ty = const_data->getType();
797 llvm::GlobalVariable* global =
798 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, ty, true, linkage_type, const_data, name);
799#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
800 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(1));
801#else
802 global->setAlignment(1);
803#endif
804 llvm::Constant* zero = ConstInt32(0);
805 llvm::Constant* indices[] = {zero, zero};
806 llvm::Constant* ptr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(ty, global, indices);
807 return ptr;
808}

819CodeGenLLVM::TypedPointer CodeGenLLVM::CreateBufferPtr(llvm::Value* buffer_ptr,
820 DataType buffer_element_dtype,
821 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> indices,
822 DataType value_dtype) {
823 ICHECK_EQ(indices.size(), 1) << "CodeGenLLVM requires all buffers to be flat 1-d buffers.";
824 llvm::Value* index = indices[0];
825
826 llvm::PointerType* buffer_ptr_type = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(buffer_ptr->getType());
827 ICHECK(buffer_ptr_type != nullptr);
828 auto address_space = buffer_ptr_type->getAddressSpace();
829
830 llvm::Type* element_type = DTypeToLLVMType(buffer_element_dtype);
831 llvm::PointerType* element_ptr_type =
832 DTypeToLLVMType(buffer_element_dtype)->getPointerTo(address_space);
833 llvm::Type* value_type = DTypeToLLVMType(value_dtype);
834 llvm::PointerType* value_ptr_type = value_type->getPointerTo(address_space);
835
836 ICHECK(index->getType()->isIntegerTy()) << "Expected buffer index to be an integer";
837
838 if (buffer_ptr_type != element_ptr_type) {
839 buffer_ptr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buffer_ptr, element_ptr_type);
840 }
841 ICHECK(!HasAlignmentPadding(buffer_element_dtype))
842 << "DType " << buffer_element_dtype
843 << " has padding for alignment. TVM data arrays are expected to be densely packed, with no "
844 "padding for alignment.";
845 llvm::Value* value_ptr = builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(element_type, buffer_ptr, index);
846
847 if (element_ptr_type != value_ptr_type) {
848 value_ptr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(value_ptr, value_ptr_type);
849 }
850
851 return TypedPointer(value_type, value_ptr);
852}

854llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::GetVarValue(const VarNode* v) const {
855 auto it = var_map_.find(v);
856 ICHECK(it != var_map_.end()) << "cannot find variable " << v->name_hint;
857 return it->second;
858}

860void CodeGenLLVM::CreatePrintf(const std::string& format,
861 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> format_args) {
862 llvm::Function* func_printf = module_->getFunction("printf");
863 if (func_printf == nullptr) {
864 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int32_, true);
865 func_printf =
866 llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, "printf", module_.get());
867 }
868
869 llvm::Function* func_fflush = module_->getFunction("fflush");
870 if (!func_fflush) {
871 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int32_, {t_void_p_}, false);
872 func_fflush =
873 llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, "fflush", module_.get());
874 }
875
876 llvm::Value* str = builder_->CreateGlobalStringPtr(format);
877 str->setName("printf_format_str");
878
879 std::vector<llvm::Value*> printf_args = {str};
880 printf_args.insert(printf_args.end(), format_args.begin(), format_args.end());
881 builder_->CreateCall(func_printf, printf_args);
882
883 // Call fflush() immediately, as this utility is intended for debug
884 // purposes. A segfault occurring within the generated LLVM code
885 // would otherwise leave the stdout buffer unflushed.
886 llvm::Value* null_stream = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(t_void_p_);
887 null_stream->setName("null_stream");
888 builder_->CreateCall(func_fflush, {null_stream});
889}

891llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateLookupReturnAddress(unsigned int level) {
892 llvm::Value* level_val = llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int32_, level);
893 llvm::Function* builtin =
894 llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module_.get(), llvm::Intrinsic::returnaddress);
895 llvm::Value* call = builder_->CreateCall(builtin, level_val);
896 call->setName("return_addr");
897
898 return call;
899}

901llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateCallExtern(Type ret_type, String global_symbol,
902 const Array<PrimExpr>& args, bool skip_first_arg) {
903 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_value;
904 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_type;
905 for (size_t i = static_cast<size_t>(skip_first_arg); i < args.size(); ++i) {
906 arg_value.push_back(MakeValue(args[i]));
907 arg_type.push_back(arg_value.back()->getType());
908 }
909 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(GetLLVMType(ret_type), arg_type, false);
910 llvm::Function* f = module_->getFunction(MakeStringRef(global_symbol));
911 if (f == nullptr) {
912 f = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, MakeStringRef(global_symbol),
913 module_.get());
914 }
915 llvm::CallInst* call = builder_->CreateCall(f, arg_value);
916 return call;
917}
918
919llvm::Function* CodeGenLLVM::GetIntrinsicDecl(llvm::Intrinsic::ID id, llvm::Type* ret_type,
920 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> arg_types) {
921 llvm::Module* module = module_.get();
922
923 if (!llvm::Intrinsic::isOverloaded(id)) {
924 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, {});
925 }
926
927 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor, 4> infos;
928 llvm::Intrinsic::getIntrinsicInfoTableEntries(id, infos);
929 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 4> overload_types;
930
931#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
932 auto try_match = [&](llvm::FunctionType* f_ty, bool var_arg) {
933 overload_types.clear();
934 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor> ref(infos);
935 auto match = llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicSignature(f_ty, ref, overload_types);
936 if (match == llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match) {
937 bool error = llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicVarArg(var_arg, ref);
938 if (error) {
939 return llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchArg;
940 }
941 }
942 return match;
943 };
944
945 // First, try matching the signature assuming non-vararg case.
946 auto* fn_ty = llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_type, arg_types, false);
947 switch (try_match(fn_ty, false)) {
948 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchRet:
949 // The return type doesn't match, there is nothing else to do.
950 return nullptr;
951 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match:
952 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
953 case llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchArg:
954 break;
955 }
956
957 // Keep adding one type at a time (starting from empty list), and
958 // try matching the vararg signature.
959 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 4> var_types;
960 for (int i = 0, e = arg_types.size(); i <= e; ++i) {
961 if (i > 0) var_types.push_back(arg_types[i - 1]);
962 auto* ft = llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_type, var_types, true);
963 if (try_match(ft, true) == llvm::Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_Match) {
964 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
965 }
966 }
967 // Failed to identify the type.
968 return nullptr;
969
970#else // TVM_LLVM_VERSION
971 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Intrinsic::IITDescriptor> ref(infos);
972 // matchIntrinsicType returns true on error.
973 if (llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicType(ret_type, ref, overload_types)) {
974 return nullptr;
975 }
976 for (llvm::Type* t : arg_types) {
977 if (llvm::Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicType(t, ref, overload_types)) {
978 return nullptr;
979 }
980 }
981 return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module, id, overload_types);
982#endif // TVM_LLVM_VERSION
983}

996void CodeGenLLVM::EmitFloat16ConversionBuiltins(bool use_float16_abi) {
997 // The LLVM IR for these function was obtained by compiling
998 //
999 // For integer ABI:
1000 // __truncXfYf2__<float, uint32_t, 23, uint16_t, uint16_t, 10>(a);
1001 // __extendXfYf2__<uint16_t, uint16_t, 10, float, uint32_t, 23>(a);
1002 // For floating-point ABI:
1003 // __truncXfYf2__<float, uint32_t, 23, _Float16, uint16_t, 10>(a);
1004 // __extendXfYf2__<_Float16, uint16_t, 10, float, uint32_t, 23>(a);
1005
1006 static const char trunc_body[] = // __truncsfhf2
1007 " %v0 = bitcast float %a0 to i32\n"
1008 " %v1 = and i32 %v0, 2147483647\n"
1009 " %v2 = add nsw i32 %v1, -947912704\n"
1010 " %v3 = add nsw i32 %v1, -1199570944\n"
1011 " %v4 = icmp ult i32 %v2, %v3\n"
1012 " br i1 %v4, label %b1, label %b5\n"
1013 "b1:\n"
1014 " %v5 = lshr i32 %v0, 13\n"
1015 " %v6 = and i32 %v5, 65535\n"
1016 " %v7 = add nuw nsw i32 %v6, -114688\n"
1017 " %v8 = and i32 %v0, 8191\n"
1018 " %v9 = icmp ugt i32 %v8, 4096\n"
1019 " br i1 %v9, label %b2, label %b3\n"
1020 "b2:\n"
1021 " %v10 = add nuw nsw i32 %v6, -114687\n"
1022 " br label %b13\n"
1023 "b3:\n"
1024 " %v11 = icmp eq i32 %v8, 4096\n"
1025 " br i1 %v11, label %b4, label %b13\n"
1026 "b4:\n"
1027 " %v12 = and i32 %v7, 65535\n"
1028 " %v13 = and i32 %v5, 1\n"
1029 " %v14 = add nuw nsw i32 %v12, %v13\n"
1030 " br label %b13\n"
1031 "b5:\n"
1032 " %v15 = icmp ugt i32 %v1, 2139095040\n"
1033 " br i1 %v15, label %b6, label %b7\n"
1034 "b6:\n"
1035 " %v16 = lshr i32 %v0, 13\n"
1036 " %v17 = and i32 %v16, 511\n"
1037 " %v18 = or i32 %v17, 32256\n"
1038 " br label %b13\n"
1039 "b7:\n"
1040 " %v19 = icmp ugt i32 %v1, 1199570943\n"
1041 " br i1 %v19, label %b13, label %b8\n"
1042 "b8:\n"
1043 " %v20 = icmp ult i32 %v1, 754974720\n"
1044 " br i1 %v20, label %b13, label %b9\n"
1045 "b9:\n"
1046 " %v21 = lshr i32 %v1, 23\n"
1047 " %v22 = sub nsw i32 113, %v21\n"
1048 " %v23 = and i32 %v0, 8388607\n"
1049 " %v24 = or i32 %v23, 8388608\n"
1050 " %v25 = add nsw i32 %v21, -81\n"
1051 " %v26 = shl i32 %v24, %v25\n"
1052 " %v27 = icmp ne i32 %v26, 0\n"
1053 " %v28 = lshr i32 %v24, %v22\n"
1054 " %v29 = zext i1 %v27 to i32\n"
1055 " %v30 = lshr i32 %v28, 13\n"
1056 " %v31 = and i32 %v28, 8191\n"
1057 " %v32 = or i32 %v31, %v29\n"
1058 " %v33 = icmp ugt i32 %v32, 4096\n"
1059 " br i1 %v33, label %b10, label %b11\n"
1060 "b10:\n"
1061 " %v34 = add nuw nsw i32 %v30, 1\n"
1062 " br label %b13\n"
1063 "b11:\n"
1064 " %v35 = icmp eq i32 %v32, 4096\n"
1065 " br i1 %v35, label %b12, label %b13\n"
1066 "b12:\n"
1067 " %v36 = and i32 %v30, 1\n"
1068 " %v37 = add nuw nsw i32 %v36, %v30\n"
1069 " br label %b13\n"
1070 "b13:\n"
1071 " %v38 = phi i32 [ %v18, %b6 ], [ %v10, %b2 ], [ %v14, %b4 ], [ %v7, %b3 ],\n"
1072 " [ 31744, %b7 ], [ 0, %b8 ], [ %v34, %b10 ], [ %v37, %b12 ],\n"
1073 " [ %v30, %b11 ]\n"
1074 " %v39 = lshr i32 %v0, 16\n"
1075 " %v40 = and i32 %v39, 32768\n"
1076 " %v41 = or i32 %v38, %v40\n"
1077 " %vlast = trunc i32 %v41 to i16\n";
1078
1079 static const char extend_body[] = // __extendhfsf2
1080 " %v1 = and i16 %vinp, 32767\n"
1081 " %v2 = zext i16 %v1 to i32\n"
1082 " %v3 = add nsw i16 %v1, -1024\n"
1083 " %v4 = icmp ult i16 %v3, 30720\n"
1084 " br i1 %v4, label %b1, label %b2\n"
1085 "b1:\n"
1086 " %v5 = shl nuw nsw i32 %v2, 13\n"
1087 " %v6 = add nuw nsw i32 %v5, 939524096\n"
1088 " br label %b6\n"
1089 "b2:\n"
1090 " %v7 = icmp ugt i16 %v1, 31743\n"
1091 " br i1 %v7, label %b3, label %b4\n"
1092 "b3:\n"
1093 " %v8 = shl nuw nsw i32 %v2, 13\n"
1094 " %v9 = or i32 %v8, 2139095040\n"
1095 " br label %b6\n"
1096 "b4:\n"
1097 " %v10 = icmp eq i16 %v1, 0\n"
1098 " br i1 %v10, label %b6, label %b5\n"
1099 "b5:\n"
1100 " %v11 = icmp ult i16 %v1, 256\n"
1101 " %v12 = lshr i32 %v2, 8\n"
1102 " %v13 = select i1 %v11, i32 %v2, i32 %v12\n"
1103 " %v14 = select i1 %v11, i32 32, i32 24\n"
1104 " %v15 = icmp ult i32 %v13, 16\n"
1105 " %v16 = lshr i32 %v13, 4\n"
1106 " %v17 = add nsw i32 %v14, -4\n"
1107 " %v18 = select i1 %v15, i32 %v13, i32 %v16\n"
1108 " %v19 = select i1 %v15, i32 %v14, i32 %v17\n"
1109 " %v20 = icmp ult i32 %v18, 4\n"
1110 " %v21 = lshr i32 %v18, 2\n"
1111 " %v22 = add nsw i32 %v19, -2\n"
1112 " %v23 = select i1 %v20, i32 %v18, i32 %v21\n"
1113 " %v24 = select i1 %v20, i32 %v19, i32 %v22\n"
1114 " %v25 = icmp ult i32 %v23, 2\n"
1115 " %v26 = sub nsw i32 0, %v23\n"
1116 " %v27 = select i1 %v25, i32 %v26, i32 -2\n"
1117 " %v28 = add nsw i32 %v27, %v24\n"
1118 " %v29 = add nsw i32 %v28, -8\n"
1119 " %v30 = shl i32 %v2, %v29\n"
1120 " %v31 = xor i32 %v30, 8388608\n"
1121 " %v32 = shl i32 %v28, 23\n"
1122 " %v33 = sub i32 1124073472, %v32\n"
1123 " %v34 = or i32 %v31, %v33\n"
1124 " br label %b6\n"
1125 "b6:\n"
1126 " %v35 = phi i32 [ %v6, %b1 ], [ %v9, %b3 ], [ %v34, %b5 ], [ 0, %b4 ]\n"
1127 " %v36 = and i16 %vinp, -32768\n"
1128 " %v37 = zext i16 %v36 to i32\n"
1129 " %v38 = shl nuw i32 %v37, 16\n"
1130 " %v39 = or i32 %v35, %v38\n"
1131 " %v40 = bitcast i32 %v39 to float\n"
1132 " ret float %v40\n"
1133 "}\n";
1134
1135 std::string short_type = use_float16_abi ? "half" : "i16";
1136
1137 std::string short_cast_in, short_cast_out;
1138 if (use_float16_abi) {
1139 short_cast_in = " %vinp = bitcast half %a0 to i16\n";
1140 short_cast_out = " %vres = bitcast i16 %vlast to half\n";
1141 } else {
1142 // No-ops that preserve the i16 values.
1143 short_cast_in = " %vinp = add i16 %a0, 0\n";
1144 short_cast_out = " %vres = add i16 %vlast, 0\n";
1145 }
1146
1147 llvm::Triple triple(llvm_target_->GetTargetTriple());
1148
1149 static const char elf_section_name[] = ".text.tvm.fp16.conv";
1150 std::string section = triple.getObjectFormat() == llvm::Triple::ELF
1151 ? std::string("section \"") + elf_section_name + "\" "
1152 : "";
1153
1154 std::string trunc_header = "define weak dso_local " + short_type +
1155 " @__truncsfhf2(float %a0) local_unnamed_addr #0 " + section +
1156 "{\nb0:\n";
1157 std::string trunc_return = " ret " + short_type + " %vres\n}\n";
1158
1159 std::string extend_header = "define weak dso_local float @__extendhfsf2(" + short_type +
1160 " %a0) local_unnamed_addr #0 " + section + "{\nb0:\n";
1161
1162 // truncate = trunc_header + trunc_body + short_cast_out + trunc_return
1163 // extend = extend_header + short_cast_in + extend_body
1164
1165 std::string attributes = "attributes #0 = { nounwind readnone \"target-cpu\"=\"" +
1166 llvm_target_->GetCPU() + "\" \"target-features\"=\"" +
1167 llvm_target_->GetTargetFeatureString() + "\" }\n";
1168
1169 auto data_layout = llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->createDataLayout();
1170 std::string module_ir = "target triple = \"" + llvm_target_->GetTargetTriple() + "\"\n" +
1171 "target datalayout = \"" + data_layout.getStringRepresentation() +
1172 "\"\n" + trunc_header + trunc_body + short_cast_out + trunc_return +
1173 extend_header + short_cast_in + extend_body + attributes;
1174
1175 auto builtins_module = llvm_target_->GetInstance().ParseIR(module_ir);
1176 link_modules_.push_back(std::move(builtins_module));
1177}
1178
1179llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::CreateIntrinsic(const CallNode* op) {
1180 if (op->op.same_as(builtin_call_llvm_intrin_) || op->op.same_as(builtin_call_llvm_pure_intrin_)) {
1181 ICHECK_GE(op->args.size(), 2U);
1182 llvm::Intrinsic::ID id = static_cast<llvm::Intrinsic::ID>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[0])->value);
1183 int64_t num_signature = Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[1])->value;
1184 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_value;
1185 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_type;
1186 for (size_t i = 2; i < op->args.size(); ++i) {
1187 arg_value.push_back(MakeValue(op->args[i]));
1188 if (i - 2 < static_cast<size_t>(num_signature)) {
1189 arg_type.push_back(arg_value.back()->getType());
1190 }
1191 }
1192 // LLVM's prefetch intrinsic returns "void", while TVM's prefetch
1193 // returns int32. This causes problems because prefetch is one of
1194 // those intrinsics that is generated automatically via the
1195 // tvm.intrin.rule mechanism. Any other intrinsic with a type
1196 // mismatch will have to be treated specially here.
1197 // TODO(kparzysz-quic): fix this once TVM prefetch uses the same
1198 // type as LLVM.
1199 llvm::Type* return_type =
1200 (id != llvm::Intrinsic::prefetch) ? GetLLVMType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)) : t_void_;
1201 llvm::Function* f = GetIntrinsicDecl(id, return_type, arg_type);
1202 ICHECK(f) << "Cannot find intrinsic declaration, possible type mismatch: "
1203#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 130
1204 << llvm::Intrinsic::getBaseName(id).str();
1205#else
1206 << llvm::Intrinsic::getName(id, {});
1207#endif
1208 return builder_->CreateCall(f, arg_value);
1209 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_and())) {
1210 return builder_->CreateAnd(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1211 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_or())) {
1212 return builder_->CreateOr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1213 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_not())) {
1214 return builder_->CreateNot(MakeValue(op->args[0]));
1215 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::bitwise_xor())) {
1216 return builder_->CreateXor(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1217 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::shift_left())) {
1218 return builder_->CreateShl(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1219 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::shift_right())) {
1220 if (op->args[0].dtype().is_int()) {
1221 return builder_->CreateAShr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1222 } else {
1223 return builder_->CreateLShr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]));
1224 }
1225 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_storage_sync())) {
1226 return CreateStorageSync(op);
1227 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::address_of())) {
1228 const BufferLoadNode* load = op->args[0].as<BufferLoadNode>();
1229 ICHECK(op->args.size() == 1 && load);
1230
1231 Array<PrimExpr> indices = load->indices;
1232 if (const RampNode* r = indices[indices.size() - 1].as<RampNode>()) {
1233 indices.Set(indices.size() - 1, r->base);
1234 }
1235
1236 std::vector<llvm::Value*> indices_val;
1237 for (const auto& index : indices) {
1238 indices_val.push_back(MakeValue(index));
1239 }
1240
1241 TypedPointer buffer_ptr = CreateBufferPtr(MakeValue(load->buffer->data), load->buffer->dtype,
1242 indices_val, load->dtype);
1243 unsigned addrspace =
1244 llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(buffer_ptr.addr->getType())->getAddressSpace();
1245 return builder_->CreatePointerCast(buffer_ptr.addr, t_char_->getPointerTo(addrspace));
1246 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::reinterpret()) && is_zero(op->args[0])) {
1247 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_void_p_);
1248 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::isnullptr())) {
1249 return builder_->CreateIsNull(MakeValue(op->args[0]));
1250 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::large_uint_imm())) {
1251 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 2U);
1252 uint64_t low = static_cast<uint64_t>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[0])->value);
1253 uint64_t high = static_cast<uint64_t>(Downcast<IntImm>(op->args[1])->value);
1254 uint64_t val = (high << 32U) | low;
1255 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype), val);
1256 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::if_then_else())) {
1257 ICHECK_EQ(op->args[0].dtype().lanes(), 1) << "if_then_else can only take scalar condition";
1258 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1259 auto* then_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_then", function_);
1260 auto* else_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_else", function_);
1261 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_end", function_);
1262 builder_->CreateCondBr(MakeValue(op->args[0]), then_block, else_block);
1263 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1264 llvm::Value* then_value = MakeValue(op->args[1]);
1265 llvm::BasicBlock* then_value_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
1266 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1267 builder_->SetInsertPoint(else_block);
1268 llvm::Value* else_value = MakeValue(op->args[2]);
1269 llvm::BasicBlock* else_value_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
1270 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1271 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
1272 llvm::PHINode* value = builder_->CreatePHI(then_value->getType(), 2);
1273 value->addIncoming(then_value, then_value_block);
1274 value->addIncoming(else_value, else_value_block);
1275 return value;
1276 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::ret())) {
1277 auto const* val = op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>();
1278 ICHECK(val) << "the tir.ret should be transformed to return zero "
1279 << "before the llvm code generation.";
1280 ICHECK_EQ(val->value, 0) << "the tir.ret should be transformed to "
1281 << "return zero before the llvm code generation.";
1282 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
1283 // LLVM allows exactly one terminator in a single basic block
1284 // append a new dummy basic block to avoid error.
1285 llvm::BasicBlock* ret_dummy =
1286 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "ret_dummy", function_);
1287 builder_->SetInsertPoint(ret_dummy);
1288 return ret_dummy;
1289 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::reinterpret())) {
1290 llvm::Type* target = DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype);
1291 return builder_->CreateBitCast(MakeValue(op->args[0]), target);
1292 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::isnan())) {
1293 // TODO(hgt312): set fast math flag
1294 llvm::Value* a = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1295 return builder_->CreateFCmpUNO(a, a);
1296 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorlow())) {
1297 llvm::Value* v = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1298 int l = GetVectorNumElements(v);
1299 return CreateVecSlice(v, 0, l / 2);
1300 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorhigh())) {
1301 llvm::Value* v = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1302 int l = GetVectorNumElements(v);
1303 return CreateVecSlice(v, l / 2, l / 2);
1304 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::vectorcombine())) {
1305 llvm::Value* v0 = MakeValue(op->args[0]);
1306 llvm::Value* v1 = MakeValue(op->args[1]);
1307 int num_elems = GetVectorNumElements(v0) * 2;
1308#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1309 std::vector<int> indices;
1310#else
1311 std::vector<unsigned> indices;
1312#endif
1313 for (int i = 0; i < num_elems; ++i) {
1314 indices.push_back(i);
1315 }
1316 return builder_->CreateShuffleVector(v0, v1, indices);
1317 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::atomic_add())) {
1318 // TODO(masahi): Support atomic for CPU backend
1319 LOG(FATAL) << "CPU backend does not support atomic add yet.";
1320 return nullptr;
1321 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::start_profile_intrinsic()) ||
1322 op->op.same_as(builtin::end_profile_intrinsic())) {
1323 LOG(INFO) << "Ignoring profile_intrinsic ... " << op->op;
1324 return nullptr;
1325 } else {
1326 LOG(FATAL) << "unknown intrinsic " << op->op;
1327 return nullptr;
1328 }
1329}

1331void CodeGenLLVM::Scalarize(const PrimExpr& e, std::function<void(int i, llvm::Value* v)> f) {
1332 if (const RampNode* ramp = e.as<RampNode>()) {
1333 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->dtype.lanes(); ++i) {
1334 PrimExpr offset = ramp->base + (ramp->stride * i);
1335 f(i, MakeValue(offset));
1336 }
1337 } else {
1338 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(e);
1339 for (int i = 0; i < e.dtype().lanes(); ++i) {
1340 f(i, builder_->CreateExtractElement(value, i));
1341 }
1342 }
1343}

1503bool CodeGenLLVM::HasAlignmentPadding(DataType dtype) {
1504 const llvm::DataLayout& data_layout = module_->getDataLayout();
1505 int bytes = data_layout.getTypeAllocSize(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype));
1506 int bytes_scalar = data_layout.getTypeAllocSize(DTypeToLLVMType(dtype.element_of()));
1507 return bytes != bytes_scalar * dtype.lanes();
1508}
1509
1510void CodeGenLLVM::BufferAccessHelper(
1511 Buffer buffer, Array<PrimExpr> indices, DataType value_dtype,
1512 std::function<llvm::Instruction*(TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int subelement_i, int alignment,
1513 bool is_volatile)>
1514 make_instruction) {
1515 DataType buffer_element_dtype = buffer->dtype;
1516
1517 ICHECK_GE(indices.size(), 1)
1518 << "Buffer " << buffer->name << " is accessed with no indices. "
1519 << "0-d scalar buffers are expected to be flattened to 1-d buffers prior to codegen.";
1520
1521 // Only the last index is allowed to be multi-lane. All earlier
1522 // indices must be scalar. This only matters for subclasses of
1523 // CodeGenLLVM, because the default implementation of GetBufferPtr
1524 // requires 1-d indices.
1525 std::vector<llvm::Value*> earlier_index_values;
1526 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size() - 1; i++) {
1527 ICHECK_EQ(indices[i].dtype().lanes(), 1)
1528 << "Buffer " << buffer->name << " is accessed with a multi-lane index at position " << i
1529 << ". Multi-lane indices are only supported as the last index.";
1530 earlier_index_values.push_back(MakeValue(indices[i]));
1531 }
1532
1533 PrimExpr last_index = indices[indices.size() - 1];
1534 ICHECK_EQ(value_dtype.lanes(), last_index.dtype().lanes() * buffer_element_dtype.lanes());
1535
1536 // Record index and elemtype in original form used for alias info
1537 PrimExpr last_index_origin = last_index;
1538 DataType buffer_element_dtype_origin = buffer_element_dtype;
1539
1540 bool is_volatile = volatile_buf_.count(buffer->data.get());
1541
1542 // If the buffer index is a contiguous ramp node, we only need to
1543 // access the first element, then cast to the value type.
1544 if (const RampNode* ramp_index = last_index.as<RampNode>()) {
1545 if (is_one(ramp_index->stride)) {
1546 last_index = ramp_index->base;
1547 }
1548 }
1549
1550 // All TVM arrays are densely packed. If the vectorized LLVM type
1551 // contains padding for alignment, we need to index based on the
1552 // size of the scalar type to avoid introducing that padding.
1553 if (last_index.dtype().lanes() == 1 && HasAlignmentPadding(buffer_element_dtype)) {
1554 last_index = buffer_element_dtype.lanes() * last_index;
1555 buffer_element_dtype = buffer_element_dtype.element_of();
1556 }
1557
1558 int alignment;
1559 if (last_index.dtype().lanes() == 1) {
1560 // If we are accessing with a single index, then the vectorized
1561 // element being accessed may require more alignment than the
1562 // underlying data type.
1563 int native_bits;
1564 GetAlignment(value_dtype, buffer->data.get(), last_index, &alignment, &native_bits);
1565 } else {
1566 // Otherwise, alignment is based on the return value's scalar
1567 // type.
1568 ICHECK_GE(value_dtype.bits(), 8);
1569 alignment = value_dtype.bits() / 8;
1570 }
1571
1572 llvm::Value* cached_vector_index = nullptr;
1573 for (int i = 0; i < last_index.dtype().lanes(); ++i) {
1574 llvm::Value* last_index_value;
1575 int subelement_i = i;
1576 if (const RampNode* ramp = last_index.as<RampNode>()) {
1577 PrimExpr offset = ramp->base + (ramp->stride * i);
1578 last_index_value = MakeValue(offset);
1579 } else if (last_index.dtype().lanes() > 1) {
1580 if (i == 0) {
1581 cached_vector_index = MakeValue(last_index);
1582 }
1583 last_index_value = builder_->CreateExtractElement(cached_vector_index, i);
1584 } else {
1585 last_index_value = MakeValue(last_index);
1586 subelement_i = -1;
1587 }
1588
1589 std::vector<llvm::Value*> all_index_values = earlier_index_values;
1590 all_index_values.push_back(last_index_value);
1591
1592 TypedPointer buffer_ptr =
1593 CreateBufferPtr(MakeValue(buffer->data), buffer_element_dtype, all_index_values,
1594 value_dtype.with_lanes(value_dtype.lanes() / last_index.dtype().lanes()));
1595 auto instruction = make_instruction(buffer_ptr, subelement_i, alignment, is_volatile);
1596 AddAliasInfo(instruction, buffer->data.get(), last_index_origin, buffer_element_dtype_origin);
1597 }
1598}
1599
1600llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) {
1601 DataType value_dtype = op->dtype;
1602
1603 std::vector<llvm::Value*> loads;
1604
1605 auto make_load = [this, &loads](TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int /* subelement_i */, int alignment,
1606 bool is_volatile) {
1607#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1608 auto load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.type, buffer_ptr.addr,
1609 llvm::Align(alignment), is_volatile);
1610#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
1611 auto load =
1612 builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.type, buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1613#else
1614 auto load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1615#endif
1616
1617 loads.push_back(load);
1618 return load;
1619 };
1620
1621 // Pass all indices into BufferAccessHelper. In CodeGenLLVM,
1622 // non-flat indices will result in an error in CreateBufferPtr, but
1623 // a subclass may override CreateBufferPtr.
1624 BufferAccessHelper(op->buffer, op->indices, value_dtype, make_load);
1625
1626 if (loads.size() == 1) {
1627 return loads[0];
1628 } else {
1629 llvm::Value* ret = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(value_dtype));
1630 for (size_t i = 0; i < loads.size(); i++) {
1631 ret = builder_->CreateInsertElement(ret, loads[i], ConstInt32(i));
1632 }
1633 return ret;
1634 }
1635}
1636
1637llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) {
1638 if (auto* ptr_op = op->op.as<OpNode>()) {
1639 auto call_op = GetRef<Op>(ptr_op);
1640 if (op->op.same_as(builtin_call_extern_) || op->op.same_as(builtin_call_pure_extern_)) {
1641 // call extern intrinsic
1642 ICHECK_GE(op->args.size(), 1U);
1643 auto global_symbol = Downcast<StringImm>(op->args[0]);
1644 return this->CreateCallExtern(GetType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)), global_symbol->value, op->args,
1645 true);
1646 } else if (op_attr_global_symbol_.count(call_op)) {
1647 // call extern if the op itself have a global symbol.
1648 return this->CreateCallExtern(GetType(GetRef<PrimExpr>(op)), op_attr_global_symbol_[call_op],
1649 op->args, false);
1650 } else {
1651 VLOG(2) << "CreateIntrinsic: " << GetRef<Call>(op);
1652 auto x = CreateIntrinsic(op);
1653 VLOG(2) << "CreateIntrinsic done";
1654 return x;
1655 }
1656 } else {
1657 ICHECK(op->op.as<GlobalVarNode>());
1658 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not yet support cross function call";
1659 return nullptr;
1660 }
1661}
1662
1663llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const RampNode* op) {
1664 llvm::Value* vec = llvm::UndefValue::get(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype));
1665 for (int i = 0; i < op->lanes; ++i) {
1666 vec = builder_->CreateInsertElement(
1667 vec, MakeValue(op->base + op->stride * make_const(op->stride.dtype(), i)), ConstInt32(i));
1668 }
1669 return vec;
1670}
1671
1672llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const ShuffleNode* op) {
1673 std::vector<llvm::Value*> vecs(op->vectors.size());
1674 int total_lanes = 0;
1675 for (int i = 0, e = op->vectors.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1676 vecs[i] = VisitExpr(op->vectors[i]);
1677 total_lanes += op->vectors[i].dtype().lanes();
1678 }
1679 llvm::Value* v0 = CreateVecConcat(vecs);
1680 std::vector<uint32_t> idx(op->indices.size());
1681 for (int i = 0, e = op->indices.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1682 const int64_t* val = as_const_int(op->indices[i]);
1683 ICHECK(val && *val >= 0 && *val < total_lanes) << "Shuffled indeces are suppose to be int, "
1684 << "but get " << op->indices[i] << "\n";
1685 idx[i] = *val;
1686 }
1687 llvm::Value* mask = llvm::ConstantDataVector::get(builder_->getContext(), idx);
1688 auto res = builder_->CreateShuffleVector(v0, llvm::UndefValue::get(v0->getType()), mask);
1689 // If the output is a single-element vector, convert it back to a scalar.
1690 if (idx.size() == 1) {
1691 res = builder_->CreateExtractElement(res, ConstInt32(0));
1692 }
1693 return res;
1694}

1696llvm::Value* CodeGenLLVM::VisitExpr_(const BroadcastNode* op) {
1697 return CreateBroadcast(MakeValue(op->value), op->lanes);
1698}

1700void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const StoreNode* op) {
1701 LOG(FATAL) << "Unexpected deprecated StoreNode. Use BufferStoreNode instead.";
1702}
1703
1704void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) {
1705 DataType value_dtype = op->value.dtype();
1706 Var buffer_var = op->buffer->data;
1707
1708 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(op->value);
1709
1710 auto make_store = [this, value](TypedPointer buffer_ptr, int subelement_i, int alignment,
1711 bool is_volatile) {
1712 llvm::Value* to_store = value;
1713 if (subelement_i != -1) {
1714 to_store = builder_->CreateExtractElement(value, subelement_i);
1715 }
1716#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1717 return builder_->CreateAlignedStore(to_store, buffer_ptr.addr, llvm::Align(alignment),
1718 is_volatile);
1719#else
1720 return builder_->CreateAlignedStore(to_store, buffer_ptr.addr, alignment, is_volatile);
1721#endif
1722 };
1723
1724 // Pass all indices into BufferAccessHelper. In CodeGenLLVM,
1725 // non-flat indices will result in an error in CreateBufferPtr, but
1726 // a subclass may override CreateBufferPtr.
1727 BufferAccessHelper(op->buffer, op->indices, value_dtype, make_store);
1728}

1730void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1731 ICHECK(is_zero(op->min));
1732 analyzer_->Bind(op->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(op->min, op->extent));
1733 if (op->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
1734 LOG(WARNING) << "Unroll hint get ignore at CodeGenLLVM backend, "
1735 << " consider set unroll_explicit=True";
1736 } else {
1737 ICHECK(op->kind == ForKind::kSerial);
1738 }
1739 CreateSerialFor(MakeValue(op->min), MakeValue(op->extent),
1740 llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(GetLLVMType(op->extent), 1), op->loop_var, op->body);
1741}
1742
1743void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const WhileNode* op) {
1744 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1745 auto* while_cond = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_cond", function_);
1746 auto* while_body = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_body", function_);
1747 auto* while_merge = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "while_merge", function_);
1748 builder_->CreateBr(while_cond);
1749 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_cond);
1750 builder_->CreateCondBr(MakeValue(op->condition), while_body, while_merge);
1751 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_body);
1752 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1753 builder_->CreateBr(while_cond);
1754 builder_->SetInsertPoint(while_merge);
1755}
1756
1757void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const IfThenElseNode* op) {
1758 llvm::Value* cond = MakeValue(op->condition);
1759 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1760 auto* then_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_then", function_);
1761 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_end", function_);
1762 if (op->else_case) {
1763 auto* else_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "if_else", function_);
1764 builder_->CreateCondBr(cond, then_block, else_block);
1765 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1766 this->VisitStmt(op->then_case);
1767 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1768 builder_->SetInsertPoint(else_block);
1769 this->VisitStmt(op->else_case.value());
1770 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1771 } else {
1772 builder_->CreateCondBr(cond, then_block, end_block, md_very_likely_branch_);
1773 builder_->SetInsertPoint(then_block);
1774 this->VisitStmt(op->then_case);
1775 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
1776 }
1777 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
1778}

1780void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* op) {
1781 auto data = op->data.value();
1782 auto array = NDArrayToLLVMArray(llvm_target_->GetContext(), data);
1783 std::string symbol_name = op->buffer_var->name_hint;
1784 llvm::GlobalVariable* param_symbol = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
1785 *module_, array->getType(), true, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, array, symbol_name);
1786
1787 var_map_[op->buffer_var.operator->()] = param_symbol;
1788 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1789}
1790
1791void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1792 ICHECK_EQ(op->extents.size(), 1)
1793 << "LLVM codegen only supports flat 1-d buffer allocation, but allocation of "
1794 << op->buffer_var->name_hint << " is " << op->extents << "-d";
1795
1796 ICHECK(!is_zero(op->condition));
1797 llvm::Value* buf = nullptr;
1798
1799 int32_t constant_size = op->ConstantAllocationSize();
1800 ICHECK_GT(constant_size, 0) << "Can only handle constant size stack allocation";
1801 StorageInfo& info = alloc_storage_info_[op->buffer_var.get()];
1802 if (constant_size % 4 == 0 && info.alignment == 0) {
1803 info.alignment = GetTempAllocaAlignment(op->dtype, constant_size);
1804 }
1805 // maximum necessary alignment in the NV devices
1806 if (info.alignment > 16) {
1807 info.alignment = 16;
1808 }
1809 llvm::AllocaInst* alloca = WithFunctionEntry([&]() {
1810 return builder_->CreateAlloca(DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype), ConstInt32(constant_size));
1811 });
1812#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1813 auto alignment = static_cast<unsigned>(alloca->getAlign().value());
1814#else
1815 unsigned alignment = alloca->getAlignment();
1816#endif
1817 if (alignment < static_cast<unsigned>(info.alignment)) {
1818#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
1819 alloca->setAlignment(llvm::Align(info.alignment));
1820#else
1821 alloca->setAlignment(info.alignment);
1822#endif
1823 }
1824#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
1825 info.alignment = static_cast<unsigned>(alloca->getAlign().value());
1826#else
1827 info.alignment = alloca->getAlignment();
1828#endif
1829
1830 buf = alloca;
1831
1832 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(
1833 buf, DTypeToLLVMType(op->dtype)->getPointerTo(buf->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()));
1834 buf->setName(op->buffer_var->name_hint.c_str());
1835
1836 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(op->buffer_var.get()));
1837 var_map_[op->buffer_var.get()] = buf;
1838 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1839}

1841void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
1842 if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
1843 IterVar iv = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node);
1844 if (iv->thread_tag.length() != 0) {
1845 if (!var_map_.count(iv->var.get())) {
1846 var_map_[iv->var.get()] = GetThreadIndex(iv);
1847 analyzer_->Bind(iv->var, Range::FromMinExtent(0, op->value));
1848 }
1849 }
1850 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::storage_alignment) {
1851 const VarNode* v = op->node.as<VarNode>();
1852 ICHECK(v);
1853 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment = static_cast<int>(op->value.as<IntImmNode>()->value);
1854 if (var_map_.count(v) && alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment > 1) {
1855 builder_->CreateAlignmentAssumption(*data_layout_, GetVarValue(v),
1856 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment);
1857 }
1858 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::volatile_scope) {
1859 const VarNode* v = op->node.as<VarNode>();
1860 ICHECK(v);
1861 volatile_buf_.insert(v);
1862 }
1863 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1864}

1866void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const AssertStmtNode* op) {
1867 With<arith::ConstraintContext> cctx(analyzer_.get(), op->condition);
1868 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1869}

1871void CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
1872 const VarNode* v = op->var.get();
1873 ICHECK(!var_map_.count(v));
1874 if (v->dtype.is_handle()) {
1875 if (!is_restricted_) {
1876 alias_var_set_.insert(v);
1877 }
1878 }
1879 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(op->value);
1880 value->setName(v->name_hint.c_str());
1881 var_map_[v] = value;
1882 analyzer_->Bind(op->var, op->value);
1883 if (alloc_storage_info_.count(v) && alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment > 1) {
1884 builder_->CreateAlignmentAssumption(*data_layout_, GetVarValue(v),
1885 alloc_storage_info_[v].alignment);
1886 }
1887 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1888}
